olive oil
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 courgette
1 bunch broccolini
1 packet garlic paste
½ lemon
1 packet Roasted Potatoes with Garlic Herb Butter
1 packet creamy pesto dressing

Combine pork and spice blend in a bowl. Drizzle with olive oil and toss.
Heat olive oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
Cook pork, until cooked through, 3-4 mins each side.
Transfer to a plate to rest.

Meanwhile, slice courgette.
Trim and halve thick broccolini lengthways.
Slice lemon into wedges.
Return pan to medium-high heat with olive oil.
Add courgette, broccolini and garlic paste and cook until tender, 4-5 mins.
Add lemon juice and season.

Prick a few holes in potato packet.
Microwave potatoes until hot and steaming, 3 mins.
Plate up pork, greens and potatoes.
Serve with creamy pesto dressing and lemon wedges.